extends ../src/jade/_internal-template

block vars
  - var activeLink = 'react';
  - var title = 'Picker Modal React Component | Framework7 React Documentation';

block content
  .docs-wrap
    .docs-nav
      include ./_docs-react-menu
    .docs-content
      h1 Picker Modal React Component
      p Picker Modal is a special overlay type which is similar to Picker/Calendar's overlay. Such modal allows to create custom picker overlays with custom content.
      p Picker Modal React component represents <a href="../docs/picker-modal.html">Picker Modal</a> component.
      h2 Usage example
      pre
        code
          :code
            <!-- Picker Modal -->
            <PickerModal>
              <!-- Picker Modal content goes here -->
            </PickerModal>
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          :code
            <!-- Picker Modal -->
            <div class="picker-modal">
              <div class="picker-modal-inner">
                <!-- Picker Modal content goes here -->
              </div>
            </div>
      h2 Properties
      table.params-table
        thead
          tr
            th Prop
            th Type
            th Description
        tbody
          tr
            td overlay
            td boolean
            td Enable to render additional picker modal overlay when required
          tr
            td theme
            td string
            td Picker Modal theme color. One of <a href="../docs/color-themes.html">default colors</a>
          tr
            td layout
            td string
            td Picker Modal layout theme. One of <a href="../docs/color-themes.html#layout-themes">default layout themes</a>
          tr
            td opened
            td boolean
            td Allows to open/close Picker Modal and set its initial state
      h2 Methods
      table.methods-table
        tr
          td .open(<span>animated</span>)
          td Open picker modal
        tr
          td .close(<span>animated</span>)
          td Close picker modal
      h2 Event Properties
      table.events-table
        thead
          tr
            th Event
            th Description
        tbody
          tr
            td picker:open
            td Event will be triggered when Picker Modal starts its opening animation
          tr
            td picker:opened
            td Event will be triggered after Picker Modal completes its opening animation
          tr
            td picker:close
            td Event will be triggered when Picker Modal starts its closing animation
          tr
            td picker:closed
            td Event will be triggered after Picker Modal completes its closing animation
      h2 Open and close Picker Modal
      p You can control Picker Modal state, open and closing it:
      ul
        li using its <a href="../docs/picker-modal.html#using-javascript">JavaScript API</a>
        li by passing <b>true</b> or <b>false</b> to its <code>opened</code> prop
        li by clicking on <a href="link.html">Link</a> or <a href="button.html">Button</a> with relevant <code>openPicker</code> property (to open it) and <code>closePicker</code> property to close it
